  "body": "## What's Changed\r\n* libdatadog upgrade to v26.0.0 by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/484\r\n* Add SA_RESETHAND to SIGSEGV handler to prevent infinite signal loop by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/488\r\n* Crash fix in case of forks: use static TLS for alloc tracking storage by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/490\r\n* Fix snprintf buffer too small in exec_ddprof() by @xroche in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/499\r\n* loader off by one heap overflow by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/503\r\n* Add Agent.md by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/505\r\n* Fix one-letter typo! by @ivoanjo in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/506\r\n* Fix exporter write error check by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/507\r\n* Fd leaks and cloexec by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/508\r\n* Add option to skip static analysis targets by @xroche in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/512\r\n* Replace non-standard ABS macro with constexpr function for C++23 compat by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/517\r\n* Target scoped cxx standard by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/515\r\n* Fix capability loss uid override by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/509\r\n* libdatadog 29.0.0: integrate libdatadog sample types by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/504\r\n* Use standard install destinations instead of ddprof/ prefix by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/518\r\n* fix: promote loader symbols to global scope before loading embedded.so (glibc) by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/524\r\n* libdatadog v30.0.0 by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/530\r\n* fix: out-of-bounds access in `process_symbolization` by @KowalskiThomas in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/533\r\n* v0.25.0 by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/532\r\n* fix: allow lazy TLS init for threads started before profiling by @nsavoire in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/531\r\n* fix: skip /tmp extraction when profiling libraries are installed by @r1viollet in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/529\r\n* loader: replace version check with SHA-256 hash verification by @nsavoire in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/534\r\n\r\n## New Contributors\r\n* @xroche made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/499\r\n* @ivoanjo made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/506\r\n* @KowalskiThomas made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/pull/533\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/DataDog/ddprof/compare/v0.23.0...v0.25.0",
